CASE ANNOUNCEMENTS

January 8, 2008

[Cite as 01108/2008 Case Announcements, 2008-0hio-18.]

DISCIPLINARY CASES

2007-0401. In re Heisler.

On April 16, 2007, this court suspended respondent, Dwight D. Heisler, Attorney Registration No. *14660029005, last known business address in Bowling Green, Ohio, for an interim period pursuant to Gov.Bar R. V(5)(A)(4). On January 4, 2008, the Board of Commissioners on Grievances and Discipline submitted a notice pursuant to Gov.Bar R. V(5)(D)(l)(c) notifying this court that respondent no longer was in default of the child support order previously submitted to the court. Upon consideration thereof,

It is ordered by the court that pursuant to Gov.Bar R. V(5)(D)(1), respondent is reinstated in this matter.

It is further ordered that pursuant to Gov.Bar R. V(5)(D)(2), this reinstatement shall not terminate respondent’s current suspension in 2006-2309, Cincinnati Bar Assn. v. Heisler, or in any pending disciplinary proceedings against respondent.

It is further ordered that the Clerk of this court issue certified copies of this order as provided for in Gov.Bar R. V(8)(D)(1), that publication be made as provided for in Gov.Bar R. V(8)(D)(2), and that respondent bear the costs of publication.
